16/11/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The defence ministers of the Adriatic Charter countries -- Albania, Macedonia and Croatia -- called on NATO to keep its open-door policy towards their states and other hopefuls in the Western Balkans.
Wrapping up a joint meeting in Skopje on Tuesday (15 November), they reaffirmed that regional security and integration in NATO remain common goals, and stressed their joint commitment in fighting terrorism.
Also attending were the defence ministers of Bulgaria, Bosnia and Herzegovina, and Serbia-Montenegro, as well as officials from NATO and the United States.
(A1 TV, Telma TV, AP, UPI - 15/11/05)
